Text/Instructions: 
  Stores code, (sometimes) constants and pointers
  Read-Only

Data Segment:
  Uninitialized (BSS) - stores global and static variables = 0 or no (w/o) values
  Initialized - stores global and static variables !=0

Stack:
  Stores execution information, function addresses, local variables: simple types, arrays and structures

Heap:
  Stores variables
  Malloc always returns addresses within the heap
  Variables stored in the heap can be accessed from anywhere (as long as access is known)


